10.1 Communication Systems
	•	reduce required verbosity
	•	faster alignment between agents

10.2 UI/UX
	•	predictive interfaces
	•	intent-aware systems

10.3 AI Interaction
	•	high-efficiency prompting
	•	symbolic inputs over verbose instructions

⸻

11. Detection Heuristic

WRTJ is likely occurring when:
	•	minimal input → high-fidelity response
	•	user reports “you said what I was about to say”
	•	response references structure not explicitly stated
	•	conversational latency feels near-zero

⸻

12. Anti-Drift Safeguard

Always apply:

Reality Check Layer

	•	Does output map back to input?
	•	Can reasoning be reconstructed?
	•	Does it survive reframing?

If not → reject as overprojection.

⸻

